HEADWORD: Harmonicon
<hw>Har*mon"i*con</hw> <pr>(-⟦icr⟧*k⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
small, flat, wind instrument of music, in which the notes are produced
by the vibration of free metallic reeds; it is now called the
<altname>harmonica</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harmonics</ent>⟦br⟧
